## Completed Work This Session

### Project: whisker — All 5 phases (Tasks #834-838)
TypeScript drop-in template engine replacing mustache.js (9.3M weekly downloads) and handlebars (28.4M weekly downloads). Zero runtime dependencies, Node.js 18+, ESM+CJS dual build.

Core: Two-phase lexer (extractTags → buildTokens) with standalone line elimination, whitespace control, custom delimiters. AST parser with section matching. Compiler with lambda support (variable re-parse, section raw block), helper integration, @data variables, expression parsing (paths, literals, subexpressions, hash pairs). Context stack with parent scope traversal, dot-notation. Full Mustache spec compliance (136/136). Handlebars extensions: helpers (simple + block), built-in helpers (if/unless/each/with/lookup/log), SafeString, @index/@key/@first/@last. Drop-in compat layers for both mustache.js and handlebars APIs. Streaming render (RenderStream extends Readable). Template precompilation CLI. Benchmark suite (640K ops/s simple interpolation).

364 tests across 8 test files. Strict TypeScript. 5 commits pushed to agentine/whisker. MIT license.

